OL,3,CPolitician apologises and admits he is
OL,4,Cfacing criminal charges
OL,6,FA longstanding Jersey politician has
OL,7,Fannounced that he is facing criminal
OL,8,Fcharges.
OL,10,FDeputy Philip Ozouf - who previously
OL,11,Fserved as the island's Assistant Chief
OL,12,FMinister - read out a personal
OL,13,Fstatement at the opening of
OL,14,FWednesday's States' meeting to say he
OL,15,Fis due to appear in the Magistrate's
OL,16,FCourt at the end of this week.
OL,18,FHe says it is in connection with
OL,19,Falleged offences under the Immigration
OL,20,FAct, relating to the employment of
OL,21,FRwandan nationals.
